 C=17|H=12|N=4\n| molecular_weight  = 272.304 g/mol\n| smiles            = C1(C2=CC=CC=C2)=NC=C3C=C(N4C=CN=C4)C=CC3=N1\n| StdInChI = 1S/C17H12N4/c1-2-4-13(5-3-1)17-19-11-14-10-15(6-7-16(14)20-17)21-9-8-18-12-21/h1-12H \n| StdInChIKey = CSZGXYBGYFNSCO-UHFFFAOYSA-N\n| bioavailability   =\n| protein_bound     =\n| metabolism        =\n| elimination_half-life =\n| excretion         =\n| pregnancy_AU      =  <!-- A / B1 / B2 / B3 / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_US      =  <!-- A / B            / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_category=\n| legal_AU          =  <!-- Unscheduled / S2 / S3 / S4 / S5 / S6 / S7 / S8 / S9 -->\n| legal_CA          =  \n| legal_UK          =  \n| legal_US          =  <!-- OTC                   / Rx-only  / Schedule I, II, III, IV, V -->\n| legal_status      =\n| routes_of_administration =\n| UNII_Ref = {{fdacite|correct|FDA}}\n}}\n\n'''CR-4056''' is an [[analgesic]] drug candidate with a novel mechanism of action, acting as a [[Ligand (biochemistry)|ligand]] for the [[imidazoline receptor]] I<sub>2</sub>. It showed promising results in animal studies against various types of [[neuropathic pain]], and has reached Phase II human [[clinical trial]]s as a potential treatment for pain associated with [[osteoarthritis]].<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Ferrari F, Fiorentino S, Mennuni L, Garofalo P, Letari O, Mandelli S, Giordani A, Lanza M, Caselli G | title = Analgesic efficacy of CR4056, a novel imidazoline-2 receptor ligand, in rat models of inflammatory and neuropathic pain | journal = Journal of Pain Research | volume = 4 | pages = 111\u201325 | date = 2011 | pmid = 21647215 | doi = 10.2147/JPR.S18353 | pmc = 3100226 }}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Li JX, Thorn DA, Qiu Y, Peng BW, Zhang Y | title = Antihyperalgesic effects of imidazoline I(2) receptor ligands in rat models of inflammatory and neuropathic pain | journal = British Journal of Pharmacology | volume = 171 | issue = 6 | pages = 1580\u201390 | date = March 2014 | pmid = 24329196 | doi = 10.1111/bph.12555 | pmc = 3954494 }}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Comi E, Lanza M, Ferrari F, Mauri V, Caselli G, Rovati LC | title = Efficacy of CR4056, a first-in-class imidazoline-2 analgesic drug, in comparison with naproxen in two rat models of osteoarthritis | journal = Journal of Pain Research | volume = 10 | pages = 1033\u20131043 | date = May 4, 2017 | pmid = 28496359 | pmc = 5422496 | doi = 10.2147/JPR.S132026 }}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Li JX | title = 2 receptors: An update | journal = Pharmacology & Therapeutics | volume = 178 | pages = 48\u201356 | date = October 2017 | pmid = 28322973 | doi = 10.1016/j.pharmthera.2017.03.009 | pmc = 5600648 }}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Rovati LC, Brambilla N, Blicharski T, Probert NJ, Vitalini C, Giacovelli G, Girolami F, D'Amato M | title = A Randomized, Placebo-Controlled, Double-Blind, Phase II Clinical Trial of the First-in-Class Imidazoline-2 Receptor Ligand CR4056 in Pain from Knee Osteoarthritis and Disease Phenotypes | journal = Arthritis Rheumatol | year = 2017 | volume = 69 (suppl 10) | location = 2017 ACR/ARHP Annual Meeting, Abstract 1193}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Imidazoline receptor modulators}}\n\n[[Category:Analgesics]]\n\n{{pharm-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Fswitzer4", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added FDA UNII (not yet published)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CR-4056"}
{"title_page": "14th Producers Guild of America Awards", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name          = 14th Annual Producers Guild Awards\n| date          = {{start date|2003|03|02}}\n| location      = [[The Century Plaza Hotel]], [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| country       = [[United States]]\n| presenter     = [[Producers Guild of America]]\n| host          = [[Patricia Heaton]]\n| award1_type   = Best&nbsp;Producer(s) Motion Picture:\n| award1_winner = ''[[Chicago (2002 film)|Chicago]]'' \u2013 [[Martin Richards (producer)|Marty Richards]]\n| previous      = [[13th Producers Guild of America Awards|13th]]\n| main          = [[Producers Guild of America Award|PGA Award]]\n| next          = [[15th Producers Guild of America Awards|15th]]\n}}\nThe '''14th Producers Guild of America Awards''' (also known as '''2003 Producers Guild Awards'''), honoring the best [[Film producer|film]] and [[television producer]]s of 2002, were held at [[The Century Plaza Hotel]] in [[Los Angeles, California]] on March 2, 2003.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNary |first1=Dave |title=Producers join 'Chicago' chorus |url=https://variety.com/2003/tv/awards/producers-join-chicago-chorus-1117881524/ |accessdate=April 10, 2020 |work=Variety |date=March 2, 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Another award for 'Chicago'|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/04/entertainment/et-quick4.1|accessdate=September 21, 2017|work=Los Angeles Times|date=March 4, 2003|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923130823/http://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/04/entertainment/et-quick4.1|archivedate=September 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Producers Guild Awards 2003 |url=http://www.producersguild.org/pg/awards_a/awards2003win.asp |publisher=Producers Guild of America |accessdate=April 10, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041211103659/http://www.producersguild.org/pg/awards_a/awards2003win.asp |archivedate=December 11, 2004 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The ceremony was hosted by [[Patricia Heaton]]. The nominees were announced on January 16, 2003.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Big pix click with PGA|url=https://variety.com/2003/film/features/big-pix-click-with-pga-1117878879/|accessdate=September 22, 2017|work=Variety|date=January 16, 2003|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923130934/http://variety.com/2003/film/features/big-pix-click-with-pga-1117878879/|archivedate=September 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Producers Guild nominates ''Chicago,'' ''Sopranos''|url=http://ew.com/article/2003/01/17/producers-guild-nominates-chicago-sopranos/|website=EW.com|accessdate=August 27, 2017|date=January 17, 2003|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516181700/http://ew.com/article/2003/01/17/producers-guild-nominates-chicago-sopranos/|archivedate=May 16, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Miramax has two contenders up for Producers Guild award|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2003/jan/18/entertainment/et-guild18|accessdate=September 21, 2017|work=Los Angeles Times|date=January 18, 2003|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402165659/http://articles.latimes.com/2003/jan/18/entertainment/et-guild18|archivedate=April 2, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=PGA Award Winners 1990-2010 - Producers Guild of America|url=http://www.producersguild.org/page/PGA_Award_19902010|website=www.producersguild.org|accessdate=August 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n===Film===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#abcdef;\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Theatrical Motion Picture|Darryl F. Zanuck Award for Outstanding Producer of Theatrical Motion Pictures]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top;\"|\n* '''''[[Chicago (2002 film)|Chicago]]'' \u2013 [[Martin Richards (producer)|Martin Richards]]'''\n** ''[[Adaptation (film)|Adaptation]]'' \u2013 [[Edward Saxon]], [[J