eyboards]]\n* Robert Bailey \u2013 background vocals\n* [[Jeff Beck]] \u2013 [[electric guitar]]\n* [[Bekka Bramlett]] \u2013 background vocals\n* Mike Brignardello \u2013 [[bass guitar]]\n* [[Tom Bukovac]] \u2013 electric guitar\n* David Campbell \u2013 string arrangements, conductor\n* Kim Fleming \u2013 background vocals\n* [[Paul Franklin (musician)|Paul Franklin]] \u2013 [[steel guitar]]\n* Reggie Hamilton \u2013 bass guitar\n* Vicki Hampton \u2013 background vocals\n* [[Dann Huff]] \u2013 electric guitar\n* David Huff \u2013 loop programming\n* Ronn Huff \u2013 string arrangements\n* [[Wynonna Judd]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* Suzie Katayama \u2013 string contractor\n* Jerry McPherson \u2013 electric guitar\n* Steve Nathan \u2013 keyboards\n* [[Don Potter (musician)|Don Potter]] \u2013 [[acoustic guitar]]\n* John \"J.R.\" Robinson \u2013 drums\n* [[Willie Weeks]] \u2013 bass guitar\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Track listings===\n'''Digital download'''\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" \u2014 5:41\n\n'''Remixes'''\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" (Piper Remix) \u2014 4:05\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" (Piper Club Mix) \u2014 7:42\n\n===Charts===\nIn the US, the song peaked at number 14 on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Billboard Adult Contemporary]] chart. On the [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', it debuted at number 50 and peaked at number 12. It is also her first single to chart in Sweden, where it debuted at number 67 and peaked at number 15.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2004/2005)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| Sweden ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://swedishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Wynonna|title=Billboard Sweden Singles Chart: Wynonna|publisher=swedishcharts.com|date= |accessdate=February 11, 2011}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 15\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]]<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=wynonna|chart=all}}|title=Billboard Chart History: Wynonna|publisher=Billboard|date= |accessdate=February 11, 2011}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 14\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2005-01-15/hot-dance-airplay |title=Dance/Mix Show Airplay : Jan 15, 2005 &#124; Billboard Chart Archive |publisher=Billboard.com |date=January 15, 2005 |accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12\n|}\n\n===Release history===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Country\n!Date\n!Format\n!Label\n|-\n|United States\n|rowspan=\"2\"|August 24, 2004<ref name=\"release wynonna\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-want-to-know-what-love-is/id81511759|title=iTunes: Wynonna \u2013 I Want to Know What Love Is \u2013 Single|publisher=iTunes|date= |accessdate=February 11, 2011}}</ref>\n|Digital download, CD single\n|[[Asylum Records|Asylum]]\n|-\n|United States\n|Remixes\n|[[Curb Records]]\n|-\n|Sweden\n|February 20, 2005\n|Digital download, CD single\n|[[Curb Records]]\n|}\n\n==Mariah Carey version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Want to Know What Love Is\n| cover      = Mariah Carey - I Want to Know What Love Is.jpg\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Mariah Carey]]\n| album      = [[Memoirs of an Imperfect Angel]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2009|09|22}}\n| format     =\n*[[CD single]]\n*[[music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2009\n*{{Duration|m=3|s=27}}\n| label      = [[Island Records|Island]]\n| writer     = [[Mick Jones (Foreigner)|Mick Jones]]\n| producer   =\n*Mariah Carey\n*[[Christopher Stewart (music producer)|C. \"Tricky\" Stewart]]\n*James \"Big Jim\" Wright\n*[[Randy Jackson]] (co.)\n| prev_title = [[Obsessed (Mariah Carey song)|Obsessed]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[H.A.T.E.U.]]\n| next_year  = 2009\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|gCadlN8fexk|\"I Want to Know What Love Is\"}}\n | type = single\n}}\n}}\n\n'''\"I Want to Know What Love Is\"''' was covered by American singer [[Mariah Carey]] and released as the second single from her twelfth studio album, ''[[Memoirs of an Imperfect Angel]]'' (2009).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/news.php?uid=2546 |title=news.news |publisher=Mariahcarey.com |accessdate=September 24, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090908203954/http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/news.php?uid=2546 |archivedate=September 8, 2009 }}</ref> The single, produced by Carey, [[Christopher Stewart (music producer)|C. \"Tricky\" Stewart]] and James \"Big Jim\" Wright, was sent to European radio stations on August 28<ref name=mariahabout>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/b/2009/08/28/mariah-carey-i-want-to-know-what-love-is-goes-to-european-radio-she-hits-it-out-of-the-park.htm |title=Mariah Carey \"I Want To Know What Love Is\" Goes to European Radio \u2013 She Hits It Out of the Park |publisher=Top40.about.com |date= |accessdate=September 24, 2009}}</ref> and first impacted U.S. radio on September 14, 2009.<ref name=mariahabout /> Mick Jones said of her version: \"I think she's actually retained the integrity of the song. You know, the arrangement is very similar to the original. They haven't tampered with the song too much. She's captured a certain emotional thing, a feeling.\"\n\n===Critical reception===\nThe single was generally well received by critics; Australian magazine ''Rhyme & Reason'' stated that \"[While Carey stayed] [...] true to the original, this piano-led remake is less an overhaul of the classic '80s hit than it is a modest but impressive update.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rhymeandreason.com.au/?p=941 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090914221223/http://www.rhymeandreason.com.au/?p=941 |url-status=dead |archive-date=September 14, 2009 |title=Exclusive Mariah Carey Album Preview \" Rhyme & Reason Magazine |publisher=Rhymeandreason.com.au |date=August 15, 2009 |accessdate=September 24, 2009 }}</ref> The UK ''[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]'' gave it a 5 out of 5 rating: \"[The song is] given the Carey treatment and [is] complete with choir and karaoke climax. It's a great rework.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/playlist/view/92758/PREVIEW-Mariah-Carey/ |title=Simply The Best 7 Days A Week :: Playlist :: PREVIEW: Mariah Carey |publisher=Daily Star |date=August 7, 2009 |accessdate=September 24, 2009}}</ref> Bill Lamb from [[About.com]] said that \"Mariah Carey's new version could leave you speechless. The diversity of vocal coloring expressed in this recording is stunning. While the single [[Obsessed (Mariah Carey song)|Obsessed]] remains disappointing, this single is a reminder of just how formidable Carey's talents are given a strong production and arrangement\".<ref name=mariahabout />\n\nWriting in a ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' music blog, Todd Martens said, \"[T]ackling a well-known power ballad seems like a safe choice. It's a comfortable fall-back plan after \"Obsessed\" performed well, but did far from blockbuster numbers. It will undoubtedly be a hit, but it's giving me more reason to fear ''Imperfect Angel''.\"<ref>Martens, Todd. [http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2009/08/mariah-carey-bets-on-nostalgia-covering-foreigner-.html Mariah Carey bets on nostalgia, covering Foreigner]. ''[[Los Angeles Times|The LA Times Music Blog]]''. August 18, 2009. Retrieved September 4, 2009.</ref>\n\n===Performances and promotion===\n* Carey debuted \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" at her ''[[Live At The Pearl]]'' concerts in the Pearl Arena at The Palms Casino & Resort, Las Vegas, on September 11 and 12, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lvrj.com/neon/58935592.html |title=SOUNDS: Mariah Carey shows at Pearl give audience chance to get close to star \u2013 Neon \u2013 ReviewJournal.com |publisher=Lvrj.com |date= |accessdate=September 24, 2009}}</ref>\n* Carey performed the song live on ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]'' on September 18.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oprah.com/media/20090918-tows-mariah-carey-i-want-to-know-what-love-is |title=Mariah Carey's I Want to Know What Love Is |publisher=Oprah.com |accessdate=September 24, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/674pk6p8V?url=http://www.oprah.com/oprahshow/Mariah-Careys-I-Want-to-Know-What-Love-Is |archivedate=April 21, 2012  }}</ref>\n* A New York radio station contest featured as its prize a mini concert by Carey at the P.C. Richard Theater in TriBeCa, New York on October 5, where she sang the song as well as \"Obsessed\" and \"H.A.T.E.U.\", also from the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/news.php?uid=2634 |title=News |publisher=Mariah Carey |accessdate=March 7, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307170943/http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/news.php?uid=2634 |archivedate=March 7, 2014 }}</ref>\n* Carey performed the single on [[X Factor (Italy)|Italy's ''X factor'']] on November 11, in the UK and in [[France]] where she did various radio interviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/news.php?uid=2690 |title=News |publisher=Mariah Carey |accessdate=March 7, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307170330/http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/news.php?uid=2690 |archivedate=March 7, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===Music video===\nCarey filmed a music video for \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" in September 2009 in New York City, directed by [[Hype Williams]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/news/4505/Mariah-Carey-Finds-Love-In-Reunion-With-Hype-Williams# |title=News &#124; Mariah Carey Finds Love In Reunion With Hype Williams |publisher=Singersroom |date=September 28, 2009 |accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\nThe video premiered on Mariah's official website on November 13, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mariahcarey.com |title=Mariah Carey Official Website: Music, Videos, Photos, Lyrics, Tour Dates, Forums |publisher=Mariahcarey.com |date= |accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\nThe video features Carey singing in [[Yankee Stadium]], intercut with shots of the audience, often accompanied by loved ones, and some glimpses into the tough times in their past, as they grow emotional from the song's performance. A gospel choir joins Carey at the center of the stadium at the video's end. Carey wears the signature curly hairstyle from the initial stages of her career circa 1990\u20131993, maintaining the ''Memoirs'' theme of the album.\n\n===Formats and track listings===\n'''Digital download'''\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" (album version) \u2014 3:26\n\n'''UK digital single'''<ref name=\"amazon.co.uk\">{{cite web |title=UK digital single |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B002WXYLNU |accessdate=January 10, 2011}} {{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" (album version) \u2014 3:26\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" ([[Moto Blanco]] Club Edit) \u2014 3:25\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" (Chew Fu Radio Fix) \u2014 3:51\n\n'''European CD single'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B002T972I8 |title=I Want To Know What Love Is \u2013 GERMAN 2track CD Single: Amazon.co.uk: Music |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\n# \"I Want to Know What Love Is\" \u2014 3:39\n# \"[[Obsessed (Mariah Carey song)|Obsessed]]\" ([[Cahill (band)|Cahill]] club edit) \u2014 6:21\n\n===Chart performance===\nThe song peaked on the US ''Billboard'' [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] chart at number 10 bringing Carey's total number of Top Ten hits on that chart to 20, one short of [[Celine Dion]]'s record. She has since surpassed this and is now tied with Celine Dion after her single \"[[Oh Santa!]]\" reached number one in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/266904/chart-beat-wednesday-miley-cyrus-mariah-carey-zac-brown-band |title=Chart Beat Wednesday: Miley Cyrus, Mariah Carey, Zac Brown Band |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref> However, it only peaked at #60 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]]. On the [[UK Singles Chart]], the song debuted at number 19 on the week ending November 29, 2009, becoming her highest debuting and peaking song since 2008's \"[[Touch My Body (Mariah Carey song)|Touch My Body]]\", which peaked at number five.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/Forever%20Faithless%20%2D%20The%20Greatest%20Hits |title=ChartArchive \u2013 The Chart Archive |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |date= |accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe song debuted at number six in France, selling 1,910 CDs in its first week and 39,720 copies in all formats as of late 2009,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ozap.com/actu/ventes-disques-france-paradis-renaud-jena-lee/315582 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121213101252/http://www.ozap.com/actu/ventes-disques-france-paradis-renaud-jena-lee/315582 |archivedate=December 13, 2012 |title=Disques : Vanessa Paradis (ne) d\u00e9tr\u00f4ne (pas) Renaud |accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infodisc.fr/Ventes_Single09.php |title=InfoDisc : Les Meilleurs Ventes de Singles en 2009 |publisher=Infodisc.fr |accessdate=March 7, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330182154/http://infodisc.fr/Ventes_Single09.php |archivedate=March 30, 2014 }}</ref> becoming the best charting version of this song there. It placed 93rd on the Year-End Chart.\n\nIn [[Brazil]], the song was boosted for its inclusion in popular [[telenovela]] ''[[Viver a Vida]]'' and stayed at number one for 27 consecutive weeks on the airplay chart, becoming the longest running number one song ever.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/i-want-know-what-love-breaks-airplay-record-brazil-54581|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307181409/http://www.mariahcarey.com/news/i-want-know-what-love-breaks-airplay-record-brazil-54581|title=I Want To Know What Love Is Breaks Airplay Record in Brazil|work=MariahCarey.com|date=April 26, 2010|archivedate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2009\u201310)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|45|artist=Mariah Carey|song=I Want To Know What Love Is}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|40|artist=Mariah Carey|song=I Want To Know What Love Is}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Belgium (Wallonia) Tip|14|artist=Mariah Carey|song=I Want To Know What Love Is}}\n|-\n|Brazil ([[Brasil Hot 100 Airplay|Hot 100 Airplay]])<ref>{{cite journal|date=January 2010|title=Brasil Hot 100 Airplay|journal=Billboard Brasil|publisher=BPP |location=Brazil|page=79|language=portuguese}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadianhot100|57|artist=Mariah Carey}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Denmark|14|artist=Mariah Carey|song=I Want To Know What Love Is}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardeuropeanhot100|16|artist=Mariah Carey}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|6|artist=Mariah Carey|song=I Want to Know What Love Is}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|37|artist=Carey, Mariah|song=I Want to Know What Love Is (2-track)|songid=615503|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Hungary ([[Mahasz]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mahasz.hu/?menu=slagerlistak&menu2=archivum&lista=kislemez&ev=2010&het=18&submit_=Keres%E9s|title=Single (track) Top 10 lista|publisher=[[Mahasz]]<!--|date=Week 18, 2010--> |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120803210827/http://www.mahasz.hu/?menu=slagerlistak&menu2=archivum&lista=kislemez&ev=2010&het=18&submit_=Keres%E9s |archivedate=August 3, 2012 |accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland3|41|artist=Mariah Carey|accessdate=January 20, 2020}}\n|-\n|align=\"left